tearing into Tin Can Tilly.

10:05.404 --> 10:07.304
Oh, this'll be good!

10:07.406 --> 10:10.603
"Who put the beans in my bindle?"

10:10.710 --> 10:14.612
"I am so tired of you saying
that I put beans in your bindle!

10:14.714 --> 10:16.614
It just makes me so"-

10:16.716 --> 10:18.707
"Do you ever shut up?"

10:18.818 --> 10:21.480
"Kiss me, you fool!"

10:25.591 --> 10:28.424
Uh, could we hear another tall tale?

10:28.527 --> 10:31.257
In a sec.

10:32.431 --> 10:34.331
<i>All righty.</i>

10:34.433 --> 10:37.129
Here's a story just for you, little girl.

10:37.236 --> 10:41.229
It's the tale ofJohnny-
No. Connie Appleseed.

10:41.340 --> 10:43.331
Oh.

10:44.810 --> 10:46.710
<i>Back around 1840...</i>

10:46.812 --> 10:49.303
<i>the great pie known as America...</i>

10:49.415 --> 10:51.883
<i>was still cooling</i>
<i>on the windowsill...</i>

10:51.984 --> 10:55.147
<i>and everybody headed west</i>
<i>for a slice.</i>

10:55.254 --> 10:59.054
# Cleaning my gun with the safety off
safety off, safety off #

10:59.158 --> 11:01.649
# Cleaning my gun with the-##

11:01.761 --> 11:03.592
Whoopsie.

11:03.696 --> 11:06.665
Dad, you just killed
a poor defenseless buffalo.

11:06.766 --> 11:08.893
A poor, delicious buffalo.

11:09.001 --> 11:13.199
He'll be dinner for the whole wagon train.

11:13.305 --> 11:15.671
- Why'd you kill another one?
- Dessert.

11:22.448 --> 11:23.881
Ow!

11:23.983 --> 11:25.917
Hey, I found a bullet.

11:28.688 --> 11:31.350
- Man, buffalo are easy to kill.
- <i>People...</i>

11:31.457 --> 11:34.654
if you don't stop this slaughter,
you'll wipe out the buffalo.

11:34.760 --> 11:38.355
Wipe out an entire species?
Why, that's impossible.

11:49.275 --> 11:53.177
Why is it we have ladders
that can put a man on the roof...

11:53.279 --> 11:56.077
but we can't find a
renewable source of food?

11:56.182 --> 11:58.548
Think, Connie. Think.

11:58.651 --> 12:00.983
- <i>Connie.</i>
- Wha-

12:01.087 --> 12:03.681
Connie.

12:03.789 --> 12:07.885
That tree! It seems to be calling to me.

12:11.797 --> 12:15.460
Of course! Apples!

12:15.568 --> 12:17.559
<i>No, Connie, over here!</i>

12:17.670 --> 12:20.230
Help me!

12:20.339 --> 12:23.137
Mom, Dad, look what I found!

12:23.242 --> 12:26.439
Oh, boy!
Buffalo testicles!

12:26.545 --> 12:30.606
- Mmm!
- No, Dad, they're apples.

12:30.716 --> 12:33.412
Yuck!

12:33.519 --> 12:37.888
Well, that's it. I don't want anything
to do with this wagon train of death.

12:37.990 --> 12:41.050
Either switch to apples,
or go on without me.

12:41.160 --> 12:43.287
Hmm!

12:45.364 --> 12:49.130
You'll be sorry!

12:51.237 --> 12:53.205
Oh!

12:54.640 --> 12:57.165
<i>So Connie roamed the prairie alone...</i>

12:57.276 --> 12:59.801
<i>planting apples seeds</i>
<i>all along the way.</i>

12:59.912 --> 13:03.575
<i>She even changed</i>
<i>her last name to Appleseed.</i>

13:03.682 --> 13:07.277
<i>And her family</i>
<i>changed theirs to Bufflekill.</i>

13:20.766 --> 13:23.826
I haven't had buffalo in six hours.
Marge...

13:23.936 --> 13:26.234
how about whipping up
some buffalo sausage...

13:26.338 --> 13:29.705
huevos buffaleros,
and some fresh-squeezed buffal-O. J?

13:29.809 --> 13:33.609
The buffalo are gone.
I think you shot them all.

13:35.681 --> 13:38.548
Oh! Connie was right!

13:38.651 --> 13:41.484
We wiped out the entire species!

13:41.587 --> 13:45.387
What have I done?
What have I done?

13:45.491 --> 13:49.291
Calm down, Pa.
There's two left.

13:52.398 --> 13:56.926
What have I done?
What have I done?

13:57.036 --> 14:00.904
<i>With the buffalo gone, the starving</i>
<i>settlers were driven to cannibalism.</i>

14:02.508 --> 14:04.976
You're the fattest, Bufflekill.

14:05.077 --> 14:07.170
Okay, everybody, dig in!

14:10.149 --> 14:12.049
<i>Stop! I've got apples!</i>

14:12.151 --> 14:14.176
Delicious, nutritious apples.

14:14.286 --> 14:16.481
And there's enough for everyone.

14:21.126 --> 14:23.060
Sweet!

14:23.162 --> 14:25.392
It's like a hootenanny in my mouth!

14:25.497 --> 14:27.556
- We're saved!
- It's a miracle!

14:27.666 --> 14:30.635
- Hooray for Connie Bufflekill!
- What?

14:30.736 --> 14:33.261
So now we're not eating Homer?

14:34.773 --> 14:36.934
And thanks to that little girl...

14:37.042 --> 14:40.170
today you can find apples
in everything that's good.

14:40.279 --> 14:42.474
Apple wine, apple whiskey...

14:42.581 --> 14:45.243
apple schnapps, apple martinis...

14:45.351 --> 14:47.717
uh, Snapple with vodka in it...

14:47.820 --> 14:49.811
apple nail polish remover-

14:49.922 --> 14:51.787
Don't forget applesauce.

14:51.891 --> 14:56.260
Yeah. I suppose you could
grind some pills into it.

14:56.362 --> 14:58.227
Aw.

15:02.568 --> 15:06.937
- Look out there, folks. That's the mighty Mississip.
- Big deal.

15:07.039 --> 15:10.440
Reminds me of a tall tale
about two scalawags...

15:10.542 --> 15:13.136
rafting down the Big Muddy-

15:13.245 --> 15:15.679
Tom Sawyer and Huck Finn.

15:15.781 --> 15:18.978
That's not a tall tale.
It's a book by Mark Twain.

15:19.084 --> 15:21.917
Look, let's just do this thing.

15:25.524 --> 15:28.618
Whitewashing sucks, Tom.
It powerful sucks.

15:28.727 --> 15:30.627
Morning, friend.

15:30.729 --> 15:33.698
Want your turn at whitewashin'?
It's powerful fun.

15:33.799 --> 15:36.927
Why, you ain't fooling me again,
Tom Sawyer.

15:37.036 --> 15:39.163
If I may.

15:39.271 --> 15:41.171
Now get to work!

15:44.410 --> 15:46.503
I still got it.

15:48.614 --> 15:51.777
Now, Huckleberry Finn,
you get down from there.

15:51.884 --> 15:54.079
A body could break his neck.

15:54.186 --> 15:56.086
I ain't afeard of that.

15:56.188 --> 15:58.952
I'd just get a new neck off n a cat.

15:59.058 --> 16:01.356
Huck!

16:01.460 --> 16:05.021
Oh, Huck, you gave your bones
an awful rattling.

16:05.130 --> 16:09.863
Yeah. But I'm feeling
better right now.

16:11.270 --> 16:13.295
- <i>Aha!</i>
- Papa!

16:13.405 --> 16:15.566
Hold my daughter's hand, will ya?

16:15.674 --> 16:18.871
I was gonna let go by-and-by.

16:18.978 --> 16:23.210
Well, I guess there's no harm done
as long as it was gonna be by-and-by.

16:23.315 --> 16:25.215
But just to play it safe-

16:25.317 --> 16:28.582
We're gathered here today to force this man...

16:28.687 --> 16:32.350
Huckleberry Finn,
into holy matrimony.

16:32.458 --> 16:35.086
How romantic.

16:35.194 --> 16:38.061
This reminds me
of our shotgun wedding.

16:38.163 --> 16:40.097
Grandpa, we've been
married for years.

16:40.199 --> 16:42.099
When are you gonna
put down that gun?

16:42.201 --> 16:45.932
Well, I reckon you're right.
Hang it all!

16:46.038 --> 16:49.838
Do you, Huck,
take Becky as your wife?

16:49.942 --> 16:52.308
Whoa!

16:52.411 --> 16:56.279
Hey, they done switched
the groom with a pig!

16:56.382 --> 16:59.510
- No wonder he was pooping so much.
- <i>Ha-ha!</i>

17:02.087 --> 17:04.646
Come on!
Let's get those polecats!

17:10.863 --> 17:14.094
Oh! Now we'll never catch 'em!

17:16.502 --> 17:20.097
I reckon we're safe now.
There's the state line.

17:25.377 --> 17:27.538
Uh-oh!
Rapids!

17:31.750 --> 17:34.810
<i>Please do not exit the raft...</i>

17:34.920 --> 17:37.821
<i>until it has come</i>
<i>to a complete stop.</i>

17:37.923 --> 17:40.585
Mr. Silas, this young lady's
flashing her privates.

17:40.692 --> 17:44.560
<i>Oh! Well, I'll dispose of this!</i>

17:44.663 --> 17:47.530
All for Silas. All for Silas.

17:53.772 --> 17:56.366
I'm considerable hungry.
We got any food left?

17:56.475 --> 17:58.409
Hmm. Looks like
we're out of corn pone...

17:58.510 --> 18:01.343
fatback, hardtack,
fat pone, "corntack."

18:01.447 --> 18:03.108
- Any "tackback"?
- "Tackback"?

18:03.215 --> 18:04.944
- I mean "backtack."
- Plumb out.

18:08.554 --> 18:11.523
One jug of whiskey,
three plugs of"tobacky"...

18:11.623 --> 18:13.750
