I can still see.

19:40.612 --> 19:42.512
That barkeep's a no-good cheat!

19:42.614 --> 19:45.014
Cheat?

19:48.887 --> 19:53.017
<i>Eh-All right.</i>
<i>We've all got derringers.</i>

19:53.125 --> 19:56.424
Now let's just put 'em away.
Nobody here is a cheat.

19:56.528 --> 19:59.361
- Cheat?
- Aw, geez.

20:02.935 --> 20:06.530
Man, those derringer bullets
are weak.

20:06.638 --> 20:08.663
Powerful weak.

20:08.774 --> 20:10.867
Light out, and stay lit out!

20:16.081 --> 20:17.981
Aw, catfish.

20:18.083 --> 20:22.577
<i>Let us pray for the souls of these</i>
<i>dearly departed young men...</i>

20:22.688 --> 20:27.387
Huckleberry Finn and Thomas Sawyer.

20:30.095 --> 20:34.122
Now for the traditional lowering
of the bodies into the coffins.

20:40.639 --> 20:43.403
And that was Tom and Huck's
last adventure.

20:43.508 --> 20:46.534
I liked that story,
'cause I was a judge.

20:46.645 --> 20:48.203
Delaware!

20:48.313 --> 20:52.773
Well, this is our stop. Would you
like to come sightseeing with us?

20:52.884 --> 20:56.786
We're gonna visit the place where
JCPenney sends their damaged merchandise.

20:56.888 --> 21:00.483
No, thanks.
I'm gonna keep on ridin' the rails...

21:00.592 --> 21:02.423
swappin' stories for sponge baths.

21:06.498 --> 21:09.592
I believe I told <i>three</i> stories.

21:10.902 --> 21:14.030
Oh!
I'll meet you in Wilmington.

21:16.508 --> 21:18.635
